<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>Richard A. Forsyth received his B.A. from the University of Michigan in 1920 and his law degree in 1922. While a student, Forsyth was a member of the Mimes and the Comedy Club. He also appeared in several Union Operas, including "Top O' The Morning." As a practicing attorney in Detroit, Forsyth was well known in amateur theater, both as actor and director, where he contributed to many stage successes.  For several years he served as President of The Players.</p>
</bioghist>



<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>The Forsyth collection includes some correspondence, journals (1914-1917), playbills from productions in the Detroit and Ann Arbor area, clippings about his theatrical career, and miscellaneous photographs.</p>
</scopecontent>

